article.description: Freshman Miroslav Stafl posted a season-high 19 points as Hartford topped Division III opponent Emerson 78-63 on Thursday.
article.headline: Stafl scores 19 to carry Hartford past Division III Emerson
article.linkText: Stafl scores 19 to carry Hartford past Division III Emerson
article.story: WEST HARTFORD, Conn. -- Freshman Miroslav Stafl posted a season-high 19 points as Hartford topped Division III opponent Emerson 78-63 on Thursday. Freshman PJ Henry also had a season-high with 15 points for Hartford (4-2). Traci Carter added 10 points, and Michael Dunne had six rebounds. Hartford led 33-30 at the break but quickly extended it to double digits after a Romain Boxus 3-pointer with nearly 16 minutes remaining. The Hawks extended their lead to 22 points, powered by Henry's six points. Zach Waterhouse had 16 points for the Lions. Nate Martin added 14 points, and Jack O'Connor had nine rebounds. Hartford takes on Merrimack at home on Sunday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- Elements of this story were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
